results.lead_paragraph: Soviet sources have begun dropping annoyed hints that they consider the Apollo 13 flight as primarily an act of political and psychological warfare against the Soviet Union. These cold war goals, they maintain, explain Washington's decision to go ahead with the flight on schedule, despite the last-hour switch of command pilots.
